description:
The Detective was drinking this
before he was killed. Could it\nhave been drugged?
name: Overturned Wine \nBottle

description:
Whoever killed the Detective 
also took his eye. They must \nknow what his powers are.
name: Missing Eye

description:
The Detective was stabbed in the
back. The killer knew to attack \nfrom where they couldn't be seen.
name: Murder Wound

description:
There are strange patterns in
the bloodstains around the \nDetective. Was he moved after\nhe was killed?
name: Drag Marks

description:
The Detective's satchel has been
searched! It's not completely\nempty but some documents are\nmissing.
name: Looted Satchel

description:
Our original tickets don't match
the room we ended up in. Were we\nmoved on purpose?
name: Old Tickets

description:
This leads into the next
passenger car. That must be \nwhere I'll find the cat.
name: Trail of \nFish Crumbs

description:
Not one hour after a cat goes
missing, and they have a bag of\ncatnip?
name: Catnip Baggie

description:
I feel sick just for holding
this. I don't have to explain\nwhat it could have been used for.
name: Dagger

description:
The ashes are still warm.
Whatever was burnt, it\nhappened recently.\nAre the twins hiding something?
name: Ashes

description:
There's no good reason for this
window to be open at this time\nof night.
name: Open Window

description:
The documents here include a
passenger list, and the\nDetective's room transfer is\nnoted down as well.
name: Clipboard

description:
I can't tell what this substance
is, but there's flecks of it near\nthe dining hall saucers.
name: Green Crumbs

description:
This might be where Snowy 
nicked the fish from. But could
he have gotten here during a 
dinner service without anyone
noticing?
name: Fish Tray

description:
There's a few different kinds
here, but none of them match the
one in our cabin. Makes it seem
like that one was specially
placed.
name: Different Wine \nBottles
